    <text id="B0005T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McDonnell announces that $100 has been authorized to purchase desks for a school
                    in Staunton.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands,<lb/>Head Quarters 9th District
                    Department of the Potomac,
                    <name type="recipient">Mr. <abbr expan="Thomas">Tho.</abbr> P.
                        Jackson<lb/>Agent<lb/>Staunton, Va.</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-10-09"><abbr expan="October">Oct.</abbr> 9<hi rend="super">th</hi> 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Winchester, Va.</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>The assistant commissioner has authorized the expenditure of $100 for furnishing
                    the schoolhouse at Staunton with desks.</p>

                <p>You are therefore directed to have desks made for this school at an expense not
                    to exceed $100-and to forward the accounts for services and material to this
                    office for payment. The account should be forwarded in time to reach the office
                    on or about the 25th of the month in which the services are rendered, or the
                    materials purchased. The purchases should be reported sooner if possible. </p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very respectfully<lb/>Your <abbr expan="Obedient">Obdt</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Servant">Svt</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>John A. McDonnell<lb/><abbr expan="Captain">Capt</abbr> &amp; <abbr
                            expan="Sub Assistant Commissioner">S.A.C.</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
